title: Grateful Dead Live at Austin Municipal Auditorium on 1972-11-22
lineage: Dat (Tascam DA-20) -> Tascam SS-R05 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, Loser, Black Throated Wind, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Beat It On Down The Line, Candyman, El Paso, Bird Song, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue, Big River, Ramble On Rose, Sugar Magnolia, Brokedown Palace, Around & Around, One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text: Promised Land According to the details, and DeadBase set 1 opens w/Promised Land, is this right or is the DeadBase wrong again ?  3 soundboards here all missing it---was it actually played ?

Fantastic I know what you mean.  There can be some annoying typos in DeadBase.  A show from 1967 without a complete song list - sure I can understand that.  But some of the others are annoying.  But to be fair there are not that many overall, I think Deadbase overall is a fantastic resource and those guys did a great job.

These Nov '72 Texas shows are all great.  Great transfer.  No Promised at this show.
